James H<//Name>
<date>1382402759093<//date><Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
Roger Shadd, the owner, is the nicest man in Yuba City. I doubt anyone who knows him  would disagree. He will go above and beyond for his clients, employees and even his community. I know that is someone we should support, when thinking about shopping local. He has tons of cleaning supplies in stock, and even equipment you can rent. If he doesn't have it, he will order it.

I feel really bad about the negative review/experience that was posted on here, as that does not represent him or his company well at all. I hope whoever handled the call has either left, or had their attitude adjusted as this cannot speak over the many good things they do there at Shadd Janitorial.

Please do not let this lone review deter you from doing business with this very deserving group. From experience, It will be beneficial to you.< /review>

He scheduled a nuclear stress test the next day along with that procedure, which somehow failed to occur (the stress test). I asked why the procedure didn't occur as scheduled and he told me it was because I did not fast...which was untrue, as I did fast and did have the implant procedure - which he did! <review>Oh boy, where do I begin...

They put me into one of the ER rooms and without doing any sort of real diagnostics put me on an IV to rehydrate me as my problem was that I was dehydrated supposedly. Didn't check my blood sugar, didn't even do an A1c. Two very basic things you do to a diabetic complaining of what might be diabetic-related complications.

Anyway while I was laying there under the IV drip half-naked because they made me put on one of those gowns, they determined that someone needed that room more than I did and kicked me out to some remote hallway that was absolutely frigid. <date>1508203636351</date>< rate>

< text>
Great little place. We decided to eat in and were greeted and seated immediately. Food was quick and (mostly) delicious especially for how cheap it was. As with Chinese places, it was hit or miss - the beef was strange and chicken in the rice and chow mein could've been left out (my girlfriend said it reminded her of what she thinks baby meat would be like. For the record, she doesn't actually know what baby is like.) If we lived closer, we would probably order from here again, keeping in mind that every dish won't be great every time.< /text>

<userid>105149578337522665914<//userid><Rate>5<//Rate><user_name>Joyce Vinnard</user_name>< review>
We ordered the Sizzling Rice and Wonton Soups, Chicken Chow Mein and Fried Rice, and Kung Pow for pick up on a Saturday night. The waiter taking my order was friendly and I waited with some cold water he got for me in the front. A good sign was that a lot of the customers were regulars known to and by the owners and wait staff- getting home the portions of food were generous , the chow mein was not greasy like some places, the fried rice was delicious (all of the food was!) We are pleased to have found a  new go to chinese food place; albeit sad that it took so long to try this place out! The soups were killer by the way.. my kids loved them too.. and all of it came to 40$ with tip.</review>

< user>
112835170709270460797<//user>
< review>
This is not a restaurant you go to if you want top of the line Chinese food. I really like this place for its lunch specials. For $5 you get an entrée with a cup of soup, an egg roll, and your choice of rice or chow mein. Sometimes your chicken looks a little less desirable than others, but they'll gladly take it back and make you a new plate until you're satisfied. The customer service is amazing and there's not a lot of people there at once so it's quiet and you get lots of attention and you get your food really fast. Take out service is available as well.< /review>

<Name>L R<//Name><time>1493917966877<//time><Rate>4</Rate>< Text>
My in-town go-to for Chinese food cravings. Food is hot and fresh most of the time and comes fairly quickly, but they usually bring your food out just one dish at a time instead of bringing all of your order out at the same time. That can be a bit frustrating during the times I come in starving but can't eat any of the main entrées (i.e. beef and broccoli) in front of me until they've brought out my accompanying side dishes (i.e. fried rice), or vice versa. Customer service is decent but nothing exceptional. The restaurant is clean and maintained to some degree but could use a decor refresh as everything seems outdated and worn.</Text>

Next time I took my daughter there, again for cleaning and a consult. I knew that my daughter needed a filling and a crown. She saw a different doctor. <date>1581105316723</date><review>Okay so this is place is definitely in the top for me. Dentist are scary even if you take 100% great care of your teeth. I had a eating disorder growing up that had destroyed my 6 front teeth. They were becoming see through on the bottoms and you could see the dentin part receding. It affected  my talking to potential jobs and just made me become extremely introverted. I'm applying to nursing school in September and I knew if I didn't fix my teeth I wasn't going to cut it through classes and progressing in my career. So we took the plunge and went to dr. Michaels. He was extremely up front about everything. He was honest, took the time to answer questions and was very caring. The hygienist were amazing and the front desk ladies are very helpful. I made the appointment for 2 weeks later and saved my money.
Day of appointment: they put me in a calming room, were extremely caring and attentive and helped keep me calm through everything. I got all 6 front teeth caped. I had temporaries put on that no one could tell were fake. ( temporary teeth suck so bad but it's only temporary and it does get better) lived off mortrin and smoothies for a week. I had the dental hygienist Michelle that put them on and she took her time making sure my bite was perfect. Nothing worst than hitting teeth when you're numb.
Last appointment: go back in for my permanent set. My goodness my gums are killing me but they got the temporary out fast and once again Michelle took her time with me and made sure everything was perfect for me. She even offered to put on temporary glue so I could make sure if the color was right. ( I didn't; the color was perfect already)
So here's what you need to take from my experience
I paid $3259.00 for 6 front teeth to be capped. I have Dental insurance but this is considered cosmetic. The worst part is hearing the noise as they grind the teeth for placement ( you're numb it's just so loud) but as of now I feel like I can finally take my life back. I can finally accept that I've truly healed from my eating issues because this closed the book on having to see the reminders each time I would  smile before. I'm so happy to finally have some of my life back. You don't realize how much of your personality sits right in your smile.
100% would do it over again if given the chance.</review><user_id>107902831172529872953<//user_id></record>

Doctors vs Hygienist: If I have a toothache they can get me in with a doctor to reccomend a few crowns or a root canal that will cost a $1,000+ within a day or two with no problem. <name>Jerrold Kazynski<//name><user>108791619027896048110< /user><Pictures>None< /Pictures><date>1613533482498<//date>< rating>
5< /rating>
< Review>
Costco has the bulk items I've come to depend upon for stocking up. Buying in bulk is retail's version of Wall Street's "dollar cost averaging." You WILL have to purchase (whatever), so buying that item in bulk on a less frequent schedule makes the cost per unit less than buying lesser quantities more often. Stock up, if it fits your living arrangement. Costco has hybridized the grocery store with the big box store.

When I pass someone in the parking lot with a limited number of items in their cart, I challenge them with: You call THAT a Costco run?

Most grin and happily admit: That's only what I need today.

Costco provides those options. A quick couple of desired items (grocery, clothing, household goods, jewelry, you name it) or a proverbial cart load or two of typically dry goods to last months-long duration. Costco is the place.<//Review>

<Name>Carmen T. Mendoza</Name><resp>None<//resp>< Review>
Costco has quite a variety of products (food, flowers, home furnishings, holiday decor, plants, clothing, prescriptions, bedding, pet care, etc.) and they always have something new. Their return policy is excellent! Their tires are comparable to any other tire place as they're not cheaper in bulk. Lines can be super smooth or super crazy, depending in what time of day you go. The convenience of having a gas station with very reasonable prices is awesome. They have lights to guide you to the stations that are empty and this helps to speed the process.< /Review>

< text>
I like this Costco. The place is huge when compared to the smaller one in Clovis on the other side of town.

My complaint here, there are almost never enough registers open to support the number of people. Today was an exception, I breezed through the checkout in about 20 minutes.

Selection is great here and in some cases they have more than the other locations I shop at most frequently.

Staff: this is a hit or miss rating because you never know what you're going to get. Unlike the Clovis store where the staff are always, and I mean always, readily available and act like they are in a good mood.

<user>104679198060475051956< /user>< user_name>
Krissy Peck< /user_name>
<Date>1545301287627< /Date><rate>3< /rate>< Text>
I LOVE this store, BUT, I had a really infuriating experience tonight.

I shop here all the time and it's always a very quick experience. And have never bought anything really expensive, the lines are pretty short, customer service is phenomenal, And only once have I ever gone there for an item and they were out of stock. I came in around 7:00 on a Wednesday because like me, most people have day jobs.

Tonight, yes I know it's only 7 days before Christmas... I came in for a couple cheap Christmas gifts but one in particular is one of the expensive items ($179.99) that you need to get from the merchandise counter after you have paid for it....First I gave them my receipt and waited almost 20 minutes before they told me they couldn't find the item in the back room.

A few minutes later there is a girl out front taking receipts and she tells me that they need to go look through the pallets in the entire store to see if they can find it. I asked for my receipt and go load up my car with the other items that I bought and come back, took maybe 8 mins, return, give them my receipt and wait... Mind you, I ordered a large pepperoni pizza when I was at the register.

Wait for another 17 minutes before they tell me they can't find my item even though they have 19 in stock in the store.  I was told to be issued a refund and that I need to call back to see if they found out where it was. I feel like they should probably be the ones calling me at this point.

Got in line to be issued a refund which took about 10 minutes because the girl they referred me to was doing other things away from the counter. Finally got my refund and found out it takes 24 to 48 hours to be refunded.  Also I was charged $199.99 instead of the $179.99 price tag.  Picked up my pizza, hardly warm to the touch of the box and drive home. COLD upon my arrival at home.  I probably should have asked for my pizza to be comped but THAT line was about 15 people long.

I feel that there could have been a lot better communication through the process of this deal and maybe they could have held my money and called ME in the morning to tell me it was in fact there and I could pick it up...or not, Then issued me a refund.

I probably won't buy anything over $100 from Costco in the future unless it's a gift card. I know it's not the fault of those specific workers, but I was extremely tired from standing on my feet all day at work and having to wait almost an hour on my feet at the end of the day was extremely frustrating for me, there are no benches near that area. I hope that they figure out a better way to locate their inventory in the future. Having 19 boxes of this tablet available I'm sure that they weren't missing entirely.

Thanks for being a productive awesome store typically, but I hope I'm the only one that has been stuck in this situation.  I was in the store a LOT longer than intended.< /Text>
